AB  - This paper considers the exact finite sample powers of some popular tests for AR(1) disturbances when heteroscedasticity is also present. Although test sizes are found to be robust, severe reductions in power are found, particularly under strong positive autocorrelation. Factors influencing these power reductions are identified analytically.
